=================================================================
  Part 5: General theorem gamma = 1/(n-m)
=================================================================

  [General theorem]
  V_eff = A*r^n + alpha*B*r^m  (A>0, B<0, n>m, 2-term structure)

  Equilibrium: dV/dr = 0
    n*A*r^(n-1) + m*alpha*B*r^(m-1) = 0
    r_0^(n-m) = -m*alpha*B / (n*A)  proportional to |alpha|   (for alpha<0)
    r_0 ∝ |alpha|^{1/(n-m)}  =>  delta = 1/(n-m)

  Critical potential V_eff^c = V_eff(r_0):
    Using equilibrium condition: m*alpha*B*r_0^m = -n*A*r_0^n
    V_eff^c = A*r_0^n + alpha*B*r_0^m = A*r_0^n*(1 - n/m)
    ∝ r_0^n ∝ |alpha|^{n/(n-m)}
    =>  gamma = n/(n-m)

  Nil3 case: n=1, m=-1
    n-m = 2
    gamma = 1/(1-(-1)) = 1/2  [EXACT ALGEBRAIC]
    delta = 1/(n-m) = 1/2     [gamma = delta, since n=1]

  Condition gamma = delta:  gamma = n/(n-m) = 1/(n-m) = delta  iff  n = 1
  => Nil3 (n=1) has gamma = delta exactly

  Geometric origin chain:
    Nil3 structure constant: C^2_01 = 1/R  (only nonzero direction)
      => Background Weyl tensor: C^2_LC(eta=V=0) = 4/(3*R^4) != 0
      => V_eff_EC = A*R^1 + B*alpha*R^(-1)  (n=1, m=-1)
      => n-m = 2  =>  gamma = delta = 1/2  (algebraically necessary)

